The paper discusses a solution for optical circuit switched data center networks, which falls under the category of network infrastructure (cs.NI) and data center architecture (cs.DC). The proposed solution involves predicting traffic matrices and designing topologies that are less sensitive to traffic changes, which involves the use of machine learning and optimization techniques, falling under the categories of signal processing (cs.SI) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the management and control of the network, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO).
